        <main id="main">
                <h1 id="title">James Madison</h1>
                <p>President, Diplomat, Founding Father<br>
                Primary Author of the Federalist Papers</p>
            <figure id="img-div">
                <img id="image" src="https://cdn.britannica.com/50/2250-004-1F1AED00/detail-James-Madison-oil-painting-Asher-B-1833.jpg?s=1500x700&q=85" alt="Portrait of James Madison - 1816."/>
                <figcaption id="img-caption">Portrait of James Madison - 1816.
                </figcaption>
            </figure>
            <section id="tribute-info">
                <h3 id="tribute-info">List of James Madison's Achievements:
                </h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Father of the Constitution: </strong>Played a crucial role in the drafting of the United States Constitution during the Constitutional Convention in 1787.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>The Federalist Papers: </strong>Co-authored, along with Alexander Hamilton and John Jay, a series of essays known as The Federalist Papers, advocating for the ratification of the Constitution.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Bill of Rights: </strong>Instrumental in the drafting and promotion of the Bill of Rights, the first ten amendments to the Constitution, which guarantee fundamental rights and liberties.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Fourth President of the United States: </strong>Served as the fourth President from 1809 to 1817.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>War of 1812: </strong>Faced the challenges of the War of 1812 during his presidency, including the burning of the White House by British forces.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Treaty of Ghent: </strong>Negotiated the Treaty of Ghent in 1814, ending the War of 1812 and restoring peaceful relations between the United States and Britain.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Founding Father: </strong>Played a crucial role in the early history of the United States and is considered one of the Founding Fathers.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Virginia Resolutions: </strong>Authored the Virginia Resolutions in opposition to the Alien and Sedition Acts, asserting the principle of nullification and states' rights.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Montpelier: </strong>Owned and operated the Montpelier estate in Virginia, contributing to agricultural and economic development.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Educational Contributions: </strong>Co-founded the University of Virginia and served as its rector, making significant contributions to education.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h3>
                    Feel free to explore more about James Madison on his <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Madison" target="_blank">Wikipedia page.</a>
                  </h3>
            </section>
